	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64534195"><p>$40B comes out to a capital LCOE of $0.16/kWh.  In rough terms that means the total wholesale operating cost of energy is in the $0.35-0.40/kWh range.  (That assumes that decommissioning cost is equal in dollar terms to the construction cost today, 30 years from now.)</p><p>If you want to make nuclear viable you need to get that capital LCOE down by about 75%.  You can save about half that with extremely streamlined permitting process, but the balance of the delta needs to come from construction efficiency improve<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64534195">

